el_questionnaire.1.player.comments_gener: It was easy and fun. The instructions were easy and straightforward to follow as well.
el_questionnaire.1.player.reasons_effort: I considered 1) cost of the investment, 2) payout to leader if succeed/fail and lastly the percentage of succeeding and failing.   Chose Investment Y at the end because the cost was relatively low (compared to X), payout to members were the same for both investments X and Y, payout to leader for Investment Y was higher than Investment X if succeed or fail. I only considered the percentage of succeeding and failing minimally as other factors were the primary factors in making my investment decision.
el_questionnaire.1.player.reasons_belief: I considered the fact that my leader participated in this experiment to win as much as possible therefore chose 0 for Q1. For Q2, there is a 50% chance that my leader chose Investment X or Y as the members payout are the same.
